                                        <p><strong>Pillayar Nonbu</p>
                                        </strong>
                                                        <p>This year's Pillaiyar Nonbu was celebrated on Dec13th, 2014 at Rean Dr, Toronto. The function was organized by Shanti Suppiah, Lakshmee Annamalai and Sindhu Suppiah. Dr. Valliappan and Mr. Annamalai distributed the elzhais to all the families who attended the event. In total 110 ezhais were distributed. Our current President Mr. Suppiah provided a year-end update on the finances of this comittee and vote of thanks. Afterwards, a Yelam (Auction) was conducted by Mr.V Pal, in which $22,030 was raised to support the CNS education fund. Several members also donated money towards the education fund. Thanks to everyone for their generous contribution. Pot-luck dinner was served. Photos of this event have been posted to the 'Photos' section within this page.</p>
                                        <p>After the function, new CNS committee was elected to serve the next term (2015-2016). Please find below the message from the <strong>incoming president Chinnameyyappan Narayanan.</strong></p>
                                        <div class="message">
                                            Hi All,<br />
                                            <p>
                                                As a new president of Canada Nagarathar Sangam and on behalf of our new committee members, I would like to thank everyone for electing us as committee members for the next two year term. We will try our best to satisfy everyone and make these 2 years as wonderful as possible. 
I am very content to proudly introduce our new committee members for all the CNS members:
                                            </p>
                                            <p><strong>Secretary: Annamalai Muthupalaniappan</strong> </p>
                                            <p><strong>Treasurer: Palaniappan Ramanathan </strong></p>
                                            <p><strong>Social Committee: Gandhimathi and Vallimayil </strong></p>
                                            <p><strong>Education committee: Geetha Ramanathan and Viji Sethuraman</strong></p>
                                            <p><strong>Editor: Periyakaruppan Subbunarayanan(PK) </strong></p>
                                            <p><strong>Youth Committee: Sindhu Suppiah, Janani Subramanian and Shangavi Kannan.</strong></p>
                                            <p><strong>NSNA Regional Representative: Subi Subramanian</strong></p>
                                            <p>We also want to thank all the past committee members for their valuable work for the Sangam in the last two years. Furthermore, we would like to thank all the volunteers that helped out in the previous term and we warmly welcome our new volunteers to support and help us in future events.</p>
                                            <p>We all sincerely thank <strong>Mr. VPal</strong> for his tremendous work on our one and only fundraising event “YELAM” to raise this record breaking income of <strong>$22,030</strong>. We also thank and appreciate everyone who contributed in the “Yelam” and their generosity to raise this money for a good cause as well as the members who donated money for the education fund to bring this target to this mark.</p>
                                            <p>Finally we want to thank everyone who attended the Pillayar Nonbu function and the election on this very special day, Dec 13, 2014. We also want to thank everyone for giving us an opportunity to serve this great “CANADA NAGARATHAR SANGAM.”</p>

                                            <p>
                                                Thank you,<br />
                                                Sincerely<br />
                                                Chinnameyyappan Narayanan<br />
                                                President<br />
                                                (On behalf of CNS Committee)<br />
                                            </p>
                                        </div>
                                        </div>
