                                        </strong>
												<p>The Bhajan for February took place at Anand and Uma's home in Cambridge.</p>

                                        <p><strong>January 2014</strong></p>

                                        <p><strong>
                                            <center>Murugan Abishekam</center></p>
                                        </strong>
												<p>What a nice way to start 2014, by going to the Temple to be part of the Murugan Abishekam.</p>
                                        <p>This year, 45 people attended the Abishekam.</p>
                                        <p>Thanks to all for the effort put in to prepare for the Abishekam, in order to receive the Lord's Blessings.</p>
                                        <p>An Abishekam is a "sacred bathing" of an Idol with milk, yoghurt, honey, and fruit juice, while priests recite mantras.</p>
                                        <p>After the Abishekam, while Lord Muruga was being "dressed", we began our traditional Bhajan.</p>
                                        <p>With a final prayer to Lord Muruga after being fully ornamented, we all went down to dining hall and enjoyed a delicious meal provided by the Temple.</p>
                                        <p>Let's all look forward to a great year!</p>
                                        <p>Please see some photos of the event, taken by Kannan, <a href="https://plus.google.com/photos/115130945402916333979/albums/5967768038557219553?authkey=CNipqrHYn46-Og">here</a>.</p>
